snippet.textDisplay: I can't say I agree with Warren that AJ needs Fury more than Fury needs AJ, I don't think it's relevant. Firstly, financially AJ is hardly going to be worried about not earning without Fury. Secondly if undisputed doesn't happen and Fury retires/vacates AJ can still fight the winner of that fight. If Fury wants undisputed it's probably now or never. Plus Warren refers to AJ as damaged goods but Fury has still never defended a title. It's not really about any of that though, all these arguments need to be left outside. An all British Undisputed fight is bigger than Hearn or Warren's egos, get it done, 50/50 split, everyone is happy. I was pleased to see Hearn praising Fury and his whole team, let's all be grown ups now.
